main event: A series of radar sightings of an unidentified object over Offutt AFB, Nebraska were reported between October 6 and October 13, 1953.
interesting points: The object was first detected suddenly on radar with no prior tracking,The object was described as disc-shaped and similar in size to a flying saucer,The object was observed traveling at speeds increasing from 200-300 miles per hour to approximately 700 miles per hour,The altitude of the object varied from 25,000 to 57,000 feet during sightings,The sightings occurred in clear weather conditions with no other aircraft in the area.
witness description: Military personnel and civilian observers with relevant experience.
